<section class="section">
 <div class="container">
 <h2 class="section-title">Our clinical and quality framework.</h2>
 <div class="grid grid--2">
 <!-- TODO: replace token with final approved MUSC wording once confirmed -->
 <div class="card"><h3>Health system selection</h3><p>MUSC Health selected CoreFlow as a home infusion partner. When an academic health system extends that trust, it sets the bar for how we handle every referral and we build to meet it.</p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Licensure</h3><p>SC Resident Pharmacy Permit issued by the SC Board of Pharmacy under Reg 99-43(B). </p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Accreditation</h3><p>Actively pursuing URAC Specialty Pharmacy v5.0 and ACHC IRX-NO797 (specialty infusion without sterile compounding), anticipated Q4 2026. <em>Accreditation has been initiated and has not yet been awarded.</em> Status documentation available to payer credentialing teams upon request.</p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Nursing model</h3><p>All infusion services delivered by CoreFlow-credentialed RNs under direct clinical supervision. CRNI-eligible credentialing required as a condition of onboarding.</p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Cold chain &amp; pharmaceutical handling</h3><p>Medications sourced as commercially manufactured, pre-compounded products with no sterile compounding. Cold chain meets USP Chapter 659 and 1079. Temperature monitoring documented for every delivery.</p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Documentation</h3><p>Clinical documentation returned to the referring prescriber after each infusion visit and made available to payer utilization management for prior authorization and concurrent review.</p></div>
 </div>
 </div>
</section>

